channel.title: My 508 Compiler doesnt work?
channel.description:
The title pretty much says it all. I can compile/run etc on 317 servers, but when it comes to 508's+ i can't compile the server.. but i can run it. What it says is "The system cannot find the specified path" or some non sense like that, i do have the latest version of JDK downloaded too..
I recently made a post on the thread on compiler questions etc and never got any kind of feed back.. So i decided to just post a topic here.. If you can help me i would greatly appreciate it.
~iDontRun

item.title: My 508 Compiler doesnt work?
item.dc:creator: @Nexus1 Nexus_
item.description:
@Nexus1 wrote:

Right click the compile tool, click edit, and it should say in the middle something like “java/jdk/7_0_3” blah blah. Then change the ending to your actual jdk version.

To find your version:
c:program files:java - should say jdk*.* blah.

Also, it may be becouse you haven’t set your envirement variables. Check out one of the programs Lin made in the download section, it should be stickies.
